\details{
Shared infrastructure for REST connectors: credential storage, sync/async
execution, and a single \code{private$.request()} funnel every endpoint method
delegates to. Venue specifics plug in by \strong{overriding two private seams} —
\code{.sign()} (how to authenticate a request) and \code{.parse_envelope()} (how to turn
a response into data and detect errors) — exactly as \link{StreamClient} subclasses
override \code{.dispatch()}. The defaults are no-auth and "JSON body, error on
non-2xx", so the base works as-is for a simple public API.
\subsection{Sync vs Async}{

\code{async = FALSE} (default) returns results directly; \code{async = TRUE} returns
\link[promises:promise]{promises::promise}s resolving to the same values. The whole class is mode-
transparent — the only branch is inside \code{\link[=then_or_now]{then_or_now()}}.
}

\subsection{Timestamp source}{

\code{time_source = "local"} (default) signs against the local UTC clock;
\code{"server"} fetches the venue's server time (\code{time_endpoint}) before each
signed request to avoid clock drift, at the cost of one extra round trip. The
source is exposed to \code{.sign()} via \code{ctx$get_timestamp_ms}.
}
}
